gomodel:SYNGO_836  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: The dopamine transporter is an integral membrane protein of the presynaptic membrane.\n\nPre-embedding immunogold and immunoperoxidase labelling demonstrates DAT-immunoreactivity predominantly along the plasma membrane of axons and axon terminals (Fig. 5-7).\n\nThe DAT antiserum is a polyclonal antiserum directed against a synthetic peptide (aa42-59; LTNSTLINPPQTPVEAQE). The specificity of the antibody was demonstrated in a previous study (See reference 1). No KO-control.. Experimental description: Twelve adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (250-400 gm) were anesthetized..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_836" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

